  "prompt": "What are Hazel eyes?",
  "response": "Hazel eyes are a unique and variable eye color characterized by a combination of colors, typically including shades of brown, green, and sometimes gold or amber. They often appear to change color depending on lighting, clothing, and surrounding colors, which can make them look different at various times. The iris of hazel eyes usually has a ring of darker color around the pupil, with lighter colors radiating outward. This variation is due to the distribution and concentration of melanin in the iris, which affects how light is absorbed and reflected. Hazel eyes are relatively uncommon and can be found in people of various ethnic backgrounds.",
